# List, Filter, Search, Sort Pattern

Follow this pattern for any list page that has filters, search, sort, or pagination. The service defines available options from the database schema; the UI reads the config and manages URL state.

## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  Config["*-config.ts\n(client-safe)"] --> Service["*.service.ts"]
  Config --> Page["page.tsx"]
  Config --> Client["client.tsx"]
  listParams["list-params.ts"] --> Service
  listParams --> Page
  listParams --> Client
```

## 1. Create a List Config File

Add `src/modules/<domain>/<context>-config.ts` (e.g. `agency-tours-config.ts`, `businesses-list-config.ts`).

- **Client-safe**: Import only `type ListConfig` from `@/modules/shared/list-params`. No server or Supabase imports.
- **Source of truth**: Filter/sort options and column names must match `database.ts` (tables, enums).
- **paramKey**: URL query param name (e.g. `status`, `tourType`). Use same key in `filters` object.
- **options**: Each option has `value`, `label`, and optional `filter` (column, operator, value). Use `value: "all"` with no `filter` for "show all".
- **searchColumns**: Columns to search with `ilike` when `search` is non-empty.

```typescript
import type { ListConfig } from "@/modules/shared/list-params"

export const agencyToursConfig: ListConfig = {
  filters: [
    {
      paramKey: "status",
      label: "Publication",
      options: [
        { value: "all", label: "All tours" },
        { value: "published", label: "Published", filter: { column: "is_active", operator: "eq", value: true } },
        { value: "unpublished", label: "Unpublished", filter: { column: "is_active", operator: "eq", value: false } },
      ],
      default: "all",
    },
  ],
  sorts: [
    { value: "created_desc", label: "Newest first", sort: { column: "created_at", ascending: false } },
    { value: "title_asc", label: "Title A–Z", sort: { column: "title", ascending: true } },
  ],
  defaultSort: "created_desc",
  searchColumns: ["title", "city"],
  pageSize: 20,
}
```

## 2. Service List Method

- Import config from the config file (not defined inline).
- Accept `ListParams & { ...extra }` (e.g. `profile`).
- Call `toQueryParams<TableRow>(config, params)` to get `{ page, pageSize, filters, sorts, or }`.
- Add implicit filters (e.g. `company_id` by role) by pushing to `qp.filters`.
- Pass result to `base.listOffset({ ...qp, select: "..." })`.
- Never create per-feature parser or URL-builder functions; use shared utilities.

```typescript
import { toQueryParams, type ListParams } from "@/modules/shared/list-params"
import { agencyToursConfig } from "./agency-tours-config"

const queryParams = toQueryParams<TourRow>(agencyToursConfig, params)
if (ownerCompanyId) queryParams.filters.push({ column: "company_id", operator: "eq", value: ownerCompanyId })
const { data, total, error } = await base.listOffset({ ...queryParams, select: AGENCY_SELECT })
```

## 3. Server Page (page.tsx)

- Use `parseListParams(config, rawSearchParams)` with raw `searchParams`.
- Pass `ListParams` to the service.
- Import config from the **config file**, not the service.

```typescript
const rawSearchParams = await searchParams
const listParams = parseListParams(agencyToursConfig, rawSearchParams)
const { data, total } = await tourService.listForAgencyPage({ ...listParams, profile })
```

## 4. Client Component

- Import config from the **config file** (keeps it client-safe; services use server-only code).
- Use `buildListUrl(basePath, config, params)` for all navigation (filters, sort, pagination).
- Render filter/sort controls by iterating `config.filters` and `config.sorts` — do not hardcode options.

```typescript
import { agencyToursConfig } from "@/modules/tours/utils/agency-tours-config"
import { buildListUrl } from "@/modules/shared/list-params"

// Select options from config
{agencyToursConfig.filters.map((f) => (
  <select key={f.paramKey} value={listParams.filters[f.paramKey]}
    onChange={(e) => navigate({ filters: { ...listParams.filters, [f.paramKey]: e.target.value }, page: 1 })}>
    {f.options.map((o) => <option key={o.value} value={o.value}>{o.label}</option>)}
  </select>
))}

router.push(buildListUrl(BASE_PATH, agencyToursConfig, { ...listParams, page: nextPage }))
```

## Variable Naming

Use full words for variables, not single letters or abbreviations. Improves readability for all devs.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
for (const f of config.filters) { ... }
const qp = toQueryParams(...)
options.map((o) => ...)

// ✅ GOOD
for (const filterDef of config.filters) { ... }
const queryParams = toQueryParams(...)
options.map((option) => ...)
```

## Don't

- Put list config inside `*.service.ts` — clients would pull in server-only code.
- Create `parseXFilter`, `parseYSort`, or `buildXUrl` per feature — use `parseListParams` and `buildListUrl`.
- Hardcode filter/sort options in the UI — read from config.
- Add per-feature `*-url.ts` files — `list-params.ts` handles all URL logic.
